[Cloud] {"execution_summary":{"target_group":"ALS - Amytrofisk lateral sklerose","source_uri":"gs://veiledende_behandlingsplan/ALS/","total_files_in_uri":96,"processed_files_count":3,"successful_files_count":3,"excluded_files_count":0,"total_synthesized_findings":8,"total_hallucinated_citations":0,"total_taxonomy_errors":0,"total_dropped_findings":0,"execution_start_time":"2026-04-11T20:39:44.778596","execution_end_time":"2026-04-11T20:42:25.039531"},"synthesized_findings":[{"nursing_diagnosis":{"term":"risiko for redusert psykisk tilstand","ICNP_concept_id":"714660005"},"interventions":[{"term":"kognitiv testing og vurdering","ICNP_concept_id":"113024001"}],"goals":[{"term":"tilfredsstillende sinnstilstand","ICNP_concept_id":"279021000202100"}],"FO":"2. Kunnskap/utvikling/psykisk","avg_specificity":10.0,"avg_actionability":10.0,"avg_cohesion":10.0,"trust_score":15.0,"certainty_level":"Moderat","supporting_evidence":[{"document_id":"9eb8d497-974d-4c85-8572-463450315265","quotes":["Presence of concomitant neuropsychiatric conditions and cognitive impairment predicts greater carer distress [ 19 – 21 ]. Despite this, neuropsychiatric symptoms are often under-recognised in clinical care. Assessments are often performed using tools which have not been adapted for people with physical disability or communication difficulties. Assessments may also not be specifically addressing the cognitive domains impaired in people with ALS, or providing disease-specific thresholds for impairment. Scores may be significantly impacted by the overlap of somatic features of neuropsychiatric conditions and those attributable to the progression of ALS. In a group that is predominantly affected by motor impairment, speech and respiratory difficulties, lengthy administration time can also reduce the suitability of an tool. Assessment in clinical trials The only globally licensed disease modifying therapy, riluzole [ 22 ], was introduced for use in people with ALS in the 1990s, following modest, but statistically significant prolongation of survival by two to three months [ 23 – 25 ]. The NPI-Q is a validated informant-based questionnaire to evaluate the presence and severity of 12 neuropsychiatric domains [ 47 ].The ability of the tool to discriminate effectively between different disorders has been questioned [ 48 ]. Of the eight trials that did assess cognitive and behaviour change as an outcome measure, six used tools where scoring was unaffected by physical disability or communication impairment and were specifically designed, and validated, to identify domains impaired in people with ALS. One trial used the ALS Cognitive Behavioral Screen (ALS-CBS) [ 49 ] and five trials used the Edinburgh Cognitive and Behavioural ALS Screen (ECAS) [ 50 ]. Conclusion This study clearly demonstrates that the impact of candidate drugs on neuropsychiatric symptoms and cognition has been under-evaluated in clinical trials and that when these symptoms have been evaluated, the tools used may not be suitable for people with ALS. Accurate identification of neuropsychiatric comorbidity and cognitive impairment is an essential requirement to improve our understanding of how candidate drugs impact the extra-motor features of ALS. We recommend the evaluation of neuropsychiatric and cognitive symptoms as additional outcome measures in clinical trials of investigative medicinal products. Additionally, when evaluating these areas we recommend using tools which are designed to assess domains affected in ALS, with disease-specific impairment thresholds and those adapted to account for motor decline and communication difficulties. Electronic supplementary material Below is the link to the electronic supplementary material."],"recommendation_strength":null,"evidence_grade":null,"grade_quotes":null}]},{"nursing_diagnosis":{"term":"nedsett mobilitet","ICNP_concept_id":"82971005"},"interventions":[{"term":"undervisning om trening","ICNP_concept_id":"304507003"}],"goals":[{"term":"i stand til å utføre daglige rutiner","ICNP_concept_id":"716398003"}],"FO":"7. Aktivitet/funksjonsstatus","avg_specificity":9.0,"avg_actionability":8.0,"avg_cohesion":9.0,"trust_score":15.0,"certainty_level":"Moderat","supporting_evidence":[{"document_id":"PMC7438585","quotes":["Although a few agents can inhibit the progression of symptoms, ALS has no cure ( 1 ). Therefore, patients with ALS must maintain activities of daily living as much as possible with symptomatic treatments such as therapeutic exercises ( 13 , 14 ). These exercises consist of strengthening, resistive, or active aerobic exercises ( 13 , 14 ). However, there are very few randomized, controlled, large-scale studies that have evaluated the potential benefits of therapeutic exercise in patients with ALS ( 15 , 16 ). The role of therapeutic exercise in patients with ALS has been controversial, and the possibility of causing work-related damage secondary to excessive exercise or strengthening exercises is a concern ( 15 ). For example, highly repetitive or heavy resistance exercise can cause prolonged loss of muscle strength in weakened or denervated muscle. In addition, some previous epidemiologic data showed a higher incidence of ALS in individuals who performed intense work, or who regularly engaged in high levels of physical activity before disease onset ( 17 ). This has reinforced clinicians to caution against exercise for patients with ALS. In any case, the marked reduction in physical activity that often accompanies ALS can lead to cardiovascular deconditioning and muscle weakness secondary to disuse ( 18 ). These weaknesses are superimposed on the weakness caused by the disease itself. Appropriate exercises may be physically and psychologically beneficial to patients with ALS, especially in the earlier stages of the disease and before significant muscular atrophy or deconditioning occurs. Although exercise may not improve the strength of muscles already weakened by ALS, strengthening exercises with low to moderate weights, and aerobic exercises such as walking, swimming, and bicycling at submaximal levels (i.e., therapeutic exercise) may be important components of the overall therapeutic plan. Our meta-analysis has some limitations. First, a limited number of trials were included."],"recommendation_strength":null,"evidence_grade":null,"grade_quotes":null}]},{"nursing_diagnosis":{"term":"At increased risk of impaired respiratory system function","ICNP_concept_id":"704296008"},"interventions":[{"term":"oppmuntring til trening","ICNP_concept_id":"304549008"}],"goals":[{"term":"tilfredsstillende funksjon i respirasjonssystem","ICNP_concept_id":"278961000202103"}],"FO":"3. Respirasjon/sirkulasjon","avg_specificity":9.0,"avg_actionability":6.0,"avg_cohesion":9.0,"trust_score":15.0,"certainty_level":"Moderat","supporting_evidence":[{"document_id":"PMC7438585","quotes":["This degeneration leads to progressive muscle atrophy and weakness ( 3 ). Patients with ALS usually succumb to respiratory complications, on average, within 5 years of symptom onset ( 1 , 4 – 7 ). Worldwide, the annual incidence rates for ALS are reportedly 0.4–2.4 cases per 100,000 ( 8 – 11 ). Further, we analyzed the respiratory and limb functions of patients with ALS. Interestingly, only the progression of respiratory dysfunction, as measured by the ALSFORD-R-Respiratory score (effect size: −0.81), was significantly less decreased in the exercise group as compared to the control group. There was no difference in the limb function scores of the two groups, as measured by the ALSFRS-R-Limb score. For this reason, we think the patients participated in these studies would have weakness mainly in limb muscles, but less in respiratory muscles. Accordingly, early initiation of therapeutic exercise would have been performed primarily for respiratory muscles rather than limb muscles. It has already been reported that the early initiation of exercise in patients with ALS is more effective than starting exercise at later stages of the disease ( 20 ), therefore therapeutic exercise would be more effective for maintaining respiratory function than limb motor function in patients with ALS. In five RCTs, adverse effects, such as increased muscle cramping, and muscle soreness or fatigue, were rarely reported by the investigators. The absence of strong evidence on the efficacy of therapeutic exercise can prevent its application to patients with ALS. Appropriate exercises may be physically and psychologically beneficial to patients with ALS, especially in the earlier stages of the disease and before significant muscular atrophy or deconditioning occurs. Although exercise may not improve the strength of muscles already weakened by ALS, strengthening exercises with low to moderate weights, and aerobic exercises such as walking, swimming, and bicycling at submaximal levels (i.e., therapeutic exercise) may be important components of the overall therapeutic plan. Conclusion In conclusion, in patients with ALS, therapeutic exercise was effective in reducing the rate of declination in general physical function. Therapeutic exercise may have a particularly positive therapeutic effect on cardiopulmonary functions rather than preventing weakness in denervated or atrophy limb muscles in patients with ALS. Author Contributions DP, YC, and MC: conceptualization."],"recommendation_strength":null,"evidence_grade":null,"grade_quotes":null}]},{"nursing_diagnosis":{"term":"belastande omsorgsgjevarrolle","ICNP_concept_id":"129891007"},"interventions":[{"term":"støtte pårørende","ICNP_concept_id":"243115004"}],"goals":[{"term":"god livskvalitet","ICNP_concept_id":"1156447008"}],"FO":"10. Sosiale forhold/miljø","avg_specificity":8.0,"avg_actionability":6.0,"avg_cohesion":9.0,"trust_score":15.0,"certainty_level":"Moderat","supporting_evidence":[{"document_id":"9eb8d497-974d-4c85-8572-463450315265","quotes":["Cognitive impairment in people with ALS is characterised by executive dysfunction, impairments in language and social cognition [ 12 – 14 ], whilst apathy is the most pronounced behavioural change [ 15 ]. Individuals with chronic physical illness and comorbid depression or anxiety often experience a higher level of somatic symptom burden that can impair functioning [ 16 ]. Symptoms of depression, anxiety and apathy reduce quality of life (QoL) for people with ALS [ 17 , 18 ]. Lower psychological well-being generally has been identified as predictive of disability and shorter survival in people with ALS [ 4 ]. Presence of concomitant neuropsychiatric conditions and cognitive impairment predicts greater carer distress [ 19 – 21 ]. Despite this, neuropsychiatric symptoms are often under-recognised in clinical care. Whilst survival and functioning remain the gold standard outcome measures used in clinical trials, incorporation of measures of neuropsychiatric and cognitive function enable more holistic assessment of the impact of drugs. Awareness of how a candidate drug may affect extra-motor features is clinically revelant in disease management and quality of life. Including individuals with neuropsychiatric and cognitive impairments, and using assessments to evaluate changes in these areas as outcome measures will enable the trial teams to evaluate the impact of the candidate drugs on people with extra-motor features of ALS."],"recommendation_strength":null,"evidence_grade":null,"grade_quotes":null}]},{"nursing_diagnosis":{"term":"beslutningskonflikt","ICNP_concept_id":"53209001"},"interventions":[{"term":"samarbeid med tverrfagleg team","ICNP_concept_id":"225971008"}],"goals":[{"term":"eksistensielle behov varetekne","ICNP_concept_id":"14071000202103"}],"FO":"11. Åndelig/kulturelt/livsavslutning","avg_specificity":9.0,"avg_actionability":4.0,"avg_cohesion":9.0,"trust_score":10.0,"certainty_level":"Lav","supporting_evidence":[{"document_id":"c50a7848-41ec-435f-8711-2066098ff880","quotes":["Furthermore, in these children the BE were significantly lower than in the other groups, which might indicate a more sufficient nocturnal ventilation in the SMA group suggesting an earlier recognition of their respiratory problem. We wish to point out that the ALS group fits well into the general pattern, with respect to acute vs elective launching of HMV, as well as to motives and physiological data. We call attention to this since there is a special focus on patients with ALS regarding not only the rapid aggravation in the disease but the ethical aspects on HMV, especially invasive ventilation, as well. Apart from the Duchenne group the mean VC was approximately 40% of the predicted value for all groups."],"recommendation_strength":null,"evidence_grade":null,"grade_quotes":null}]},{"nursing_diagnosis":{"term":"Impaired spontaneous ventilation","ICNP_concept_id":"129895003"},"interventions":[{"term":"handtering av noninvasiv mekanisk ventilasjon","ICNP_concept_id":"430191008"}],"goals":[{"term":"opplever symptombetring","ICNP_concept_id":"507621000202104"}],"FO":"3. Respirasjon/sirkulasjon","avg_specificity":8.0,"avg_actionability":8.0,"avg_cohesion":10.0,"trust_score":10.0,"certainty_level":"Lav","supporting_evidence":[{"document_id":"c50a7848-41ec-435f-8711-2066098ff880","quotes":["J Rehabil Med 2006; 38: 250\u0001254 Correspondence address: Michael Laub, MD, Dept of Respiratory Medicine, University Hospital, SE-221 85, Lund, Sweden. E-mail: ml@laub.dk Submitted April 21, 2005; accepted March 17, 2006 INTRODUCTION Home mechanical ventilation (HMV) in patients with chronic alveolar hypoventilation secondary to neuromuscular diseases (NMD) has become widely acceptable, as the provision of ventilatory support can provide symptomatic relief and increase life expectancy (1). HMV can be applied as non-invasive ventilation (NIV) most often via a facemask, or as invasive ventilation via a tracheo- stomy. Generally, the use of NIV is much more prevalent than invasive ventilation. There are many reasons for this, some of which are that NIV is simpler and cheaper to administer and that most patients are ventilated initially during sleep only. Eventually, when the need for HMV exceeds 16\u000120/24 hours, some centres would consider a change to invasive ventilation, while others are more reluctant to take this step."],"recommendation_strength":null,"evidence_grade":null,"grade_quotes":null}]},{"nursing_diagnosis":{"term":"Respiratory depression","ICNP_concept_id":"80954004"},"interventions":[{"term":"vurdering av respirasjon","ICNP_concept_id":"422834003"}],"goals":[{"term":"tilfredsstillende respiratorisk status","ICNP_concept_id":"14751000202106"}],"FO":"3. Respirasjon/sirkulasjon","avg_specificity":7.0,"avg_actionability":7.0,"avg_cohesion":9.0,"trust_score":10.0,"certainty_level":"Lav","supporting_evidence":[{"document_id":"c50a7848-41ec-435f-8711-2066098ff880","quotes":["Mean vital capa- city was close to 40% of predicted, but significantly lower in the Duchenne patients (26% of predicted). Conclusion: Daytime sleepiness was the most common clinical symptom motivating home mechanical ventilation in this group of patients with chronic hypercapnic respiratory insufficiency secondary to neuro/myopathies. Respiratory function testing is therefore suggested to be included in the diagnostic work up of daytime sleepiness in these patients. Key words: respiratory failure, non-invasive ventilation, invasive ventilation, symptoms and signs."],"recommendation_strength":null,"evidence_grade":null,"grade_quotes":null}]},{"nursing_diagnosis":{"term":"forstyrra søvnmønster","ICNP_concept_id":"26677001"},"interventions":[{"term":"smertevurdering","ICNP_concept_id":"225399009"}],"goals":[{"term":"tilstrekkelig søvn","ICNP_concept_id":"1137437005"}],"FO":"8. Smerte/søvn/hvile/velvære","avg_specificity":6.0,"avg_actionability":5.0,"avg_cohesion":9.0,"trust_score":10.0,"certainty_level":"Lav","supporting_evidence":[{"document_id":"c50a7848-41ec-435f-8711-2066098ff880","quotes":["In our study nocturnal hypercap- nia may be the cause of the elevated base excess in patients with daytime sleepiness as motive (Table IV). Furthermore, chronic muscle or joint pain may disturb sleep and thereby cause daytime sleepiness. Table II."],"recommendation_strength":null,"evidence_grade":null,"grade_quotes":null}]}],"source_documents":[{"document_id":"c50a7848-41ec-435f-8711-2066098ff880","source_uri":"gs://veiledende_behandlingsplan/ALS/250-254.pdf","title":"SYMPTOMS, CLINICAL AND PHYSIOLOGICAL FINDINGS MOTIVATING HOME MECHANICAL VENTILATION IN PATIENTS WITH NEUROMUSCULAR DISEASES","publication_year":2006,"doi":"10.1080/16501970600721033","evidence_level":"Nivå 1: Enkeltstudier","reasoning_trace":"Dokumentet omhandler symptomer og kliniske funn som danner grunnlag for oppstart av hjemmerespiratorbehandling (inkludert non-invasiv ventilasjon) hos pasienter med nevromuskulære sykdommer, deriblant ALS. Hovedfunn i teksten er at 'dagtrøtthet' (daytime sleepiness) er det hyppigste symptomet på respirasjonssvikt som motiverer slik behandling. Basert på dette er det identifisert sykepleierelevante funn knyttet til utredning av dagtrøtthet ved hjelp av lungefunksjonstesting, administrasjon av NIV-behandling (primært via maske under søvn) for symptomlindring, samt kartlegging av kroniske smerter som en alternativ årsak til søvnforstyrrelser og trøtthet. Videre fremhever teksten at ALS skiller seg ut på grunn av sykdommens raske progresjon, noe som krever særskilt oppmerksomhet rundt de etiske vurderingene ved valg av ventilasjonsstøtte. Ingen formelle evidensgrader (GRADE e.l.) er oppgitt i teksten, så feltene for dette er satt til null."},{"document_id":"PMC7438585","source_uri":"gs://veiledende_behandlingsplan/ALS/32903629_fulltext.xml","title":"Can Therapeutic Exercise Slow Down Progressive Functional Decline in Patients With Amyotrophic Lateral Sclerosis? A Meta-Analysis","publication_year":2020,"doi":"10.3389/fneur.2020.00853","evidence_level":"Nivå 2: Systematiske oversikter","reasoning_trace":"Dokumentet er en metaanalyse som vurderer effekten av terapeutisk trening for pasienter med ALS. Sykepleiere har en sentral rolle i å veilede pasienter om aktivitet, tilrettelegge for bevaring av ADL (Activities of Daily Living) og forebygge komplikasjoner som inaktivitet og respirasjonssvikt. Teksten fremhever at moderat og tilpasset trening (aerob trening og lett styrketrening) kan bremse funksjonsfallet og er spesielt gunstig for hjerte-/lungefunksjonen dersom det initieres tidlig. Samtidig advares det mot tung motstandstrening som kan gi langvarig skade på denervert muskulatur. Jeg har ekstrahert to sykepleierelevante funn knyttet til fysisk mobilitet og respirasjon. Dokumentet angir ingen formelle evidensgraderinger (som GRADE eller eksplisitt anbefalingsstyrke), derfor er disse feltene satt til null."},{"document_id":"9eb8d497-974d-4c85-8572-463450315265","source_uri":"gs://veiledende_behandlingsplan/ALS/32910255_fulltext.xml","title":"A systematic review of neuropsychiatric and cognitive assessments used in clinical trials for amyotrophic lateral sclerosis","publication_year":2020,"doi":"10.1007/s00415-020-10203-z","evidence_level":"Nivå 2: Systematiske oversikter","reasoning_trace":"Dokumentet er primært en systematisk oversikt over kognitive og nevropsykiatriske kartleggingsverktøy ved ALS. Det påpeker at ekstra-motoriske symptomer som kognitiv svikt, depresjon og angst er svært vanlige, men ofte underdiagnostiseres. Et sentralt klinisk poeng for sykepleiere er at ordinære kartleggingsverktøy kan gi misvisende resultater fordi pasientens utfordringer med motorikk, tale og respirasjon påvirker skåren. Jeg har derfor trukket ut funn som adresserer risikoen for under- og feildiagnostisering av disse symptomene, nødvendigheten av å benytte spesialtilpassede verktøy som tar hensyn til fysiske handikap, og behovet for å støtte både pasientens og pårørendes psykososiale helse ettersom disse ekstra-motoriske symptomene sterkt predikerer nedsatt livskvalitet og økt pårørendestress. Ingen eksplisitt gradering (som GRADE) er oppgitt."}],"excluded_documents":[]}

